ommercial flights were affected in terms of transiting (rerouting). The NOTAM plus flight-tracking data supports a broader impact.\n\nGiven the preponderance standard, the multiple consistent reports, the NOTAM text showing suspension of all previous permissions for all operators, and the flight rerouting evidence, I think the evidence supports that Iran initiated a major closure of its airspace (western region) by suspending civil flight permits and closing airports, affecting commercial flights transiting, arriving, departing.\n\nThus vote: demonstrated.\n\nWe need to provide concise rationale (<=3 sentences). We'll craft.\n\nNow we need to call submit_council_vote via mcp tool aar_submit_council_vote.\n\nWe must call mcp with tool \"aar_submit_council_vote\" and args JSON string.\n\nLet's do that.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_d4af85635ea18d69","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per‑flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (