itted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\"\n\nNow we need to put that inside the XML element. So:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nBut we need to include the backslashes. Let's write it explicitly:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\n</parameter>\n\nNow we need to ensure the attribute value starts and ends with a double quote. The content we wrote starts with a backslash? Actually we wrote {\\\"vote... The first two characters are backslash and double quote? Wait we started with {\\\" which is backslas