ot disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nBut we need to ensure the attribute value is a JSON object. The attribute value should be the JSON object text. We need to wrap the attribute value in quotes? In the mcp call, the args attribute expects a string that is the JSON object. In the earlier successful call to aar_wait_for_opportunity, we used args: {} (empty braces) without quotes. That suggests that the args attribute value is not quoted; it's directly the JSON text. In the XML, we wrote:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{}\n</parameter>\n\nThat passed an empty JSON object. So we should do similarly: provide the JSON object directly between the tags.\n\nThus we need to write:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nNow we must ensure that the content is valid JSON. It starts with {, ends with }. Inside we have \"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"...\". The rationale string contains double quotes? We have none. It contains parentheses, commas, periods, but no double quotes. So it's fine.\n\nThus we need to pass that.\n\nLet's try.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781916640142,"responseId":"gen-1781916640-5ts5CsZWLqfpj1BOXqD8","responseModel":"nvidia/nemotron-3-s