\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nNow we must ensure that the content is valid JSON. It starts with {, ends with }. Inside we have \"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"...\". The rationale string contains double quotes? We have none. It contains parentheses, commas, periods, but no double quotes. So it's fine.\n\nThus we need to pass that.\n\nLet's try.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_ac0868e77359f568","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":29613,"output":1108,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":30721,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781916640142,"responseId":"gen-1781916640-5ts5CsZWLqfpj1BOXqD8","responseModel":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b-20230311"}}
