{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"thinking_start","contentIndex":0,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The system still sees the first character as a single quote? Actually we passed args as a dict again. I notice that in our args we are still using the dict syntax because we wrote args: {'vote': ..., 'rationale': ...}. We need to change the content to be the JSON object text, not a dict.\n\nLet's manually type the exact text we want inside the <parameter=args> element.\n\nWe'll write:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nMake sure there is no extra whitespace before the first { or after the last }. Let's do that exactly.\n\nNow we need to escape any double quotes inside the attribute? The attribute value is the text between the tags. If we include double quotes inside, they are part of the value. The XML parser will see the opening tag <parameter=args> then the content starts with a double quote? Actually the first character after the opening tag is a double quote? We start with {, not a quote. So the attribute value begins with {. That's fine; the attribute value is a string that starts with {.\n\nThus we need to write:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. Thi