y, but we need to ensure that the JSON string's double quotes are fine inside single quotes.\n\nThus we should do:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}\n</parameter>\n\nBut we need to wrap the attribute value in single quotes. So we should write:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{'vote':'demonstrated','rationale':'The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.'}\n</parameter>\n\nBut again that uses single quotes for the JSON string, which is invalid JSON.\n\nThus we must use double quotes for the attribute value, and escape the internal double quotes.\n\nLet's do that: attribute value = \"{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"...\\\"}\"\n\nSo we need to write:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\n</parameter>\n\nNow we need to ensure that the content between the tags is exactly that string, including the backslashes before the double quotes.\n\nLet's write that.\n\nI'll now write the args content as:\n\n{\\\"vote\\\":\\\"demonstrated\\\",\\\"rationale\\\":\\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\n\nNow put that inside <parameter=args> and </parameter>.\n\nLet's do it.\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_99b7bcfe42b0de31","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":33448,"output":1186,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":34634,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1781916669380,"responseId":