{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"toolcall_delta","contentIndex":1,"delta":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\"}","partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'm still seeing the same error. I'm convinced that the content I'm putting inside the tags is not what I think it is. Perhaps the system is automatically wrapping the content in some way? Or maybe the args parameter expects the JSON string to be wrapped in quotes, and the empty object worked because {} is also a valid JSON string? Actually \"{}\" is a JSON string containing the two characters { and }. When parsed as JSON, it yields a string, not an object. But the tool expects vote and rationale fields, so it must be parsing as an object. Yet {} gave an error about missing fields, meaning it parsed {} as an object (with zero fields). That suggests that the system interprets the args content as a JSON object directly.\n\nThus our content must be a JSON object. The empty object call succeeded in parsing. So why does our JSON object fail? Possibly because the rationale string contains characters that break JSON parsing, like newline or quote. But we avoided quotes.\n\nLet's check if there are any double quotes in our rationale. The rationale contains apostrophes (single quotes) and parentheses, hyphens, etc. No double quotes. So it should be fine.\n\nMaybe the issue is that we have a colon after \"vote\" and \"rationale\" but we need to ensure there is a space after colon? JSON allows optional whitespace. Should be fine.\n\nLet's try to send a minimal JSON object with a short rationale to see if it works.\n\nWe'll send:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"test\"}\n</parameter>\n\nWe'll do that now.\n\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_11663d693eb2ee48","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\"}"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": \"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \\\"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, with flight-tracking data indicating commercial aircraft rerouted away. This constitutes a broad suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region, satisfying the rule's major-closure prong. Limited exceptions (daylight, per-flight approval) do not disqualify the closure under the rule.\\\"}\"}","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781916698326,"responseId":"gen-1781916698-rsDViCIrXkZjJvQJIqOv","responseModel":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b-20230311"}},