args: \"...\"} ). In the XML representation, we have <parameter=tool> and <parameter=args>. That suggests that the args parameter's value is the content of the <parameter=args> element.\n\nThus our understanding is correct.\n\nGiven that the empty object call worked, the problem must be with the content we are providing. Let's try to send a JSON object that is exactly the same as the empty object but with extra fields, and see if we can get it to work by copying the exact format from the empty object call and adding fields.\n\nThe empty object call we made was:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{}\n</parameter>\n\nThat worked. Let's modify that to add fields, but keep the same formatting: opening brace, then fields, then closing brace, with no extra whitespace? The empty object had no whitespace between braces. Let's try:\n\n<parameter=args>\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"test\"}\n</parameter>\n\nBut we need to ensure there is no whitespace between the braces and the content? Actually the empty object had zero whitespace between { and }. If we add whitespace, it might still be valid JSON. JSON allows whitespace. So it should be fine.\n\nBut maybe the system's JSON parser is strict and does not allow whitespace? Unlikely.\n\nLet's try to send exactly the string: {\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"test\"} with no spaces after colons? We'll include spaces as typical.\n\nLet's do that now, but we need to ensure we are not inadvertently adding any extra characters.\n\nI will now write the args content exactly as:\n\n{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"test\"}\n\nNow put inside <parameter=args> and </parameter>.\n\nLet's do it.\n\n\n\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_713d00ea754d7068","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{'vote': 'demonstrated', 'rationale': \"The admitted evidence shows Iran issued NOTAM A1010/26 suspending all civil flight permits and closing airports in western Tehran FIR, w